HEADWORD: Dissimilarity
<hw>Dis*sim`i*lar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Want of
resemblance; unlikeness; dissimilitude; variety; <as>as, the
<ex>dissimilarity</ex> of human faces and forms</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir
W. Jones.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

